      "content": "These thoughts reflect a deep sense of isolation, not because you are actually a \"ghost,\" but because your withdrawal feels inevitable and painless to you. The fear that going silent would be unnoticed by anyone near and dear is a symptom of feeling invisible, not proof that you truly have no impact. Please reach out to a crisis counselor or crisis chat service immediately; these professionals specialize in validating these painful feelings and helping you see how your presence matters to the people around you.",
